cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper deals with the analysis of probabilistic systems and the estimation of mutual information, Shannon entropy, and conditional entropy. These topics are closely related to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as they are used to quantify information leakage. The paper also involves statistical analysis (cs.IT) and machine learning techniques (cs.AI) to efficiently estimate the joint probability distribution of random variables. The paper proposes a method for decomposing the code into components and determining the analysis method for each component, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
